Mixin (recommended)Return a viewMeta.cli_view only <p>Return plain data; the mixin sets <code>cli_view</code> and renders automatically:</p> <pre><code>class App(ListViewMixin, Parser):
    def cli_run(self, **_):
        return [{"name": "ada"}, {"name": "linus"}]
</code></pre> <p>Build the view yourself (still works with or without a mixin):</p> <pre><code>from clak import Parser
from clak.views import ListView

class App(Parser):
    def cli_run(self, **_):
        return ListView(
            [{"name": "ada"}, {"name": "linus"}],
            columns=["name"],
        )
</code></pre> <p>No mixin flags — configure the view class yourself:</p> <pre><code>from clak import Parser
from clak.views import ListView

class App(Parser):
    class Meta:
        cli_view = ListView

    def cli_run(self, **_):
        return [{"name": "ada"}, {"name": "linus"}]
</code></pre>
